vysotsky in english arts at stanford university presented by sica home search this site arts enews subscribe calendar vysotsky in english friday february 3 2012 7 00pm bechtel conference center encina hall the concert is free and open to the public please join us friday february 3rd for a concert by vadim astrakhan a singer guitarist translator who has made it his life's ambition to integrate vladimir vysotsky's work into world culture by translating his songs into english and performing them in a modern musical manner astrakhan has received rave reviews for his translations and his show which is now coming to california for the first time with a show at stanford vladimir vysotsky 1938 1980 remains a tremendous folk legend in russia where he is considered the nation's greatest poet singer songwriter and bard of the 20th century though his work which contained social and political commentary was officially largely ignored by the soviet cultural establishment it has had an immeasurable influence on russian culture to this day the concert is free and open to the public sponsored by creees center for russian east european & eurasian studies click for more information home calendar gallery news visiting artists grants organizations facilities plan a visit about sica students faculty staff make a gift volunteer login press sitemap contact connect twitter facebook vimeo flickr 2011 stanford university all rights reserved local user login
